1
00:00:07,375 --> 00:00:10,609
<i>I always said I'd
be happier alone.</i>

2
00:00:10,711 --> 00:00:13,078
<i>I'd have my work, my friends.</i>

3
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:17,416
<i>But someone in
your life all the time?</i>

4
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:21,136
<i>- More trouble than it's worth.</i>
<i>- </i> OK. Crib goes here.

5
00:00:21,238 --> 00:00:22,838
<i>Apparently, I got over it.</i>

6
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:27,709
Changing table
will go... right here.

7
00:00:29,563 --> 00:00:32,831
But you can't plan a baby
room before you have a baby.

8
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,544
I mean, you're gonna
jinx the adoption.

9
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:37,408
The social worker wants to see
where we live. This is like a death-trap.

10
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,354
I'm trying to create a
reasonable distraction.

11
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:42,774
- Hello?
- Janet! Welcome!

12
00:00:42,860 --> 00:00:47,579
How are you? Thanks for coming
out. Oh, be careful. Watch those nails.

13
00:00:55,488 --> 00:00:57,639
Perfect for a baby, right?

14
00:00:59,176 --> 00:01:00,308
Hm...

15
00:01:06,067 --> 00:01:09,147
I'm gonna stop in the lab. I'll
see you after the intake, OK?

16
00:01:09,203 --> 00:01:12,220
OK. Oh, God. I forgot it
was the Hobarts today.

17
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:15,957
It always bums me out when we have
an Alzheimer's patient with young kids.

18
00:01:16,059 --> 00:01:17,820
There's no shame in sitting
this one out. I can do the intake.

19
00:01:17,844 --> 00:01:20,646
Stop treating me like I'm your
wife. On the trial, I'm a colleague.

20
00:01:20,748 --> 00:01:23,526
I'm allowed to say, "It bums me out."
It doesn't mean you have to feed me

21
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:25,895
warm milk and run a
bath. Treat me like a doctor.

22
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:29,187
Right. Sorry. OK. Go
do the intake, colleague.

23
00:01:30,691 --> 00:01:34,209
Shepherd, you got a minute? I
need to talk to you about your trial.

24
00:01:34,311 --> 00:01:35,877
Oh, um...

25
00:01:35,979 --> 00:01:37,790
I should get Meredith.
I just got a lecture on

26
00:01:37,814 --> 00:01:40,610
the failure to extend professional
courtesy to one's spouse.

27
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:43,868
I think it's best you
don't get Meredith.

28
00:01:47,174 --> 00:01:51,643
You're in, in very good hands. I still
feel bad that I'm not gonna be here.

29
00:01:51,745 --> 00:01:55,980
For the surgery? I'll be unconscious,
that's not when I'm gonna miss you.

30
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:59,434
- OK. Then I guess I won't...
- You can feel bad

31
00:01:59,537 --> 00:02:01,003
about all the time that follows.

32
00:02:01,105 --> 00:02:04,790
When I'm not under general
anesthesia, and you're still not here,

33
00:02:04,891 --> 00:02:08,527
you're halfway around
the world... with Arnold.

34
00:02:08,629 --> 00:02:11,029
- Andrew.
- Ah...

35
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:13,699
- Excuse me?
- He's a rock star.

36
00:02:13,801 --> 00:02:16,513
I kind of feel like the sound of an
adoring crowd should follow his name.

37
00:02:16,537 --> 00:02:19,938
I don't... Is that a
compliment or an insult?

38
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:22,518
I don't know, I guess it depends
on how you feel about rock stars.

39
00:02:22,542 --> 00:02:24,688
- OK, well,
Andrew's not a rock star...
- Ah...

40
00:02:24,712 --> 00:02:26,990
OK, you know what? Can you stop
that? It's starting to get annoying.

41
00:02:27,014 --> 00:02:30,232
My wife's leaving, I'm
allowed to be annoying.

42
00:02:33,837 --> 00:02:37,517
I'm not a real wife, so that
doesn't buy for a lot of bad behavior.

43
00:02:37,591 --> 00:02:39,791
Well, you're my real best
friend, what does that get me?

44
00:02:40,811 --> 00:02:44,195
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be. Go be happy.

45
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:46,181
With Andrew. Ah...

46
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,834
You're impossible.

47
00:02:54,908 --> 00:02:56,975
Yeah. You, too.

48
00:02:58,228 --> 00:03:02,397
Meredith, tell me
exactly what you did.

49
00:03:02,499 --> 00:03:04,982
- I can't tell you.
- We can still fix this,

50
00:03:05,085 --> 00:03:07,330
- but I need to know
what you did.
- If I tell you,

51
00:03:07,354 --> 00:03:10,188
- it'll make it worse.
- It's worse already. Meredith...

52
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:12,690
Listen, I... I love you.

53
00:03:12,792 --> 00:03:17,195
And I'm sorry, but I
can't tell you anything.

54
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:24,786
You want to be treated like a colleague?
I'm gonna treat you like a colleague.

55
00:03:24,888 --> 00:03:29,791
Alex Karev informed Dr. Hunt that
Dr. Grey tampered with my clinical trial.

56
00:03:29,893 --> 00:03:32,828
She switched around the
placebos and the drugs,

57
00:03:32,930 --> 00:03:36,031
probably invalidating my trial.

58
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:40,485
- Is this true?
- Nothing
I did has any effect...

59
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:42,704
- Tell me exactly what happened.
- I can't do that.

60
00:03:42,822 --> 00:03:45,523
Do you have any idea what
you've done? You think the FDA

61
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,942
will get anywhere near
this hospital ever again?

62
00:03:48,044 --> 00:03:50,078
Meredith, look at me.

63
00:03:52,415 --> 00:03:55,267
If this is wrong, if there
is something going on,

64
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:59,804
if Karev is exaggerating, this is
the part where you have to tell me.

65
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,840
This is the part where you
have to deny the charges.

66
00:04:02,926 --> 00:04:05,360
Kick me off the study.

67
00:04:05,462 --> 00:04:08,964
There's nothing
wrong with the study.

68
00:04:09,066 --> 00:04:13,268
- Nothing I did
changes anything.
- But you're not denying it.

69
00:04:15,438 --> 00:04:19,190
I'm gonna have to investigate
what's going on here,

70
00:04:19,292 --> 00:04:22,627
but it looks to me like
you just lost your job.

71
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:34,085
So they're probably gonna
fire me. Are you happy?

72
00:04:34,141 --> 00:04:36,119
- Come on, they're not gonna...
- I want your crap

73
00:04:36,143 --> 00:04:38,343
out of my house by
the end of the day.

74
00:04:39,897 --> 00:04:44,465
What the hell was that?

75
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:48,619
A 757 went down in the Sound.

76
00:04:48,721 --> 00:04:51,473
We're looking at about
200 injured passengers.

77
00:04:51,575 --> 00:04:54,876
We're the designated crisis center.
Families will be instructed to come here

78
00:04:54,978 --> 00:04:58,730
to find their loved ones. We
are activating Surge Protocol.

79
00:04:58,832 --> 00:05:01,850
Dr. Hunt is gonna be running
the show. It's gonna be chaotic.

80
00:05:01,952 --> 00:05:05,002
You need to listen carefully,
you need to stay focused,

81
00:05:05,104 --> 00:05:07,272
do not contribute to the panic.

82
00:05:07,374 --> 00:05:09,140
Get to your stations.

83
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:12,177
Dr. Bailey, clear
any beds that we can.

84
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:14,946
- Discharge or transfer.
- OK. Uh, Grey.

85
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:19,434
All right, Torres, you'll be with
me. Kepner, set up the ER for triage.

86
00:05:19,536 --> 00:05:21,046
Other Grey, I want you
running the family center.

87
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,588
Take over in the
cafeteria. Yang, blood bank.

88
00:05:23,691 --> 00:05:26,124
- We might need a Candyman.
- Dr. Sloan'll be our Candyman.

89
00:05:26,226 --> 00:05:28,021
Let's be liberal with
pain meds for our victims

90
00:05:28,045 --> 00:05:32,180
and sedatives for patients that we're
moving. Avery, you can help him out.

91
00:05:32,282 --> 00:05:35,200
- Let's move, people!
- What happened with Meredith?

92
00:05:35,302 --> 00:05:37,218
- Cristina, I can't...
- Owen!

93
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:41,222
She tampered with Shepherd's
study, invalidated the results.

94
00:05:41,324 --> 00:05:42,607
She destroyed the whole thing.

95
00:05:48,832 --> 00:05:51,177
There was a plane crash. They're
gonna cancel your procedure

96
00:05:51,201 --> 00:05:54,163
and try to send you home. You
need to tell them that you're a D-1.

97
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:57,472
You don't need to be in pre-op, but
you want to be moved to a regular room.

98
00:05:57,574 --> 00:06:00,241
That way, when the hospital
starts doing surgery again,

99
00:06:00,344 --> 00:06:03,060
- you'll be first in the queue.
- Don't you have a plane...?

100
00:06:03,162 --> 00:06:06,498
- Wait, did they
shut down the airport?
- No, but we're not leaving

101
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:10,518
till it's over. They need
surgeons and trauma counselors.

102
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,020
These are your films.

103
00:06:12,122 --> 00:06:14,522
They're gonna schedule your
surgery at Seattle Presbyterian.

104
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:15,802
Seattle Pres can't take anymore,

105
00:06:15,826 --> 00:06:17,808
- start calling County!
- Avery!

106
00:06:17,894 --> 00:06:20,411
Why'd you give me that guy in
the middle of a mass trauma?

107
00:06:20,497 --> 00:06:22,525
- Avery?
- - The kid quit Webber's study.

108
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,189
What kind of idiot decides
working with the chief of surgery's

109
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:26,484
too taxing on his schedule?

110
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:28,786
He didn't quit 'cause he
thinks it's too much hard work.

111
00:06:28,856 --> 00:06:31,706
He quit because he thinks the
chief has a shot at a Harper Avery.

112
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:36,077
He was worried that if his name was
on it, it would kill Webber's chances.

113
00:06:38,015 --> 00:06:40,982
- Kepner! Discharges.
- Yep.

114
00:06:46,690 --> 00:06:50,075
You know, she's the only one
who ever gave a rat's ass about you.

115
00:06:50,177 --> 00:06:52,727
And now you might
have destroyed her career.

116
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,640
You should find some
skanky intern to love you,

117
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,342
'cause next time you're
in a burning building,

118
00:06:56,366 --> 00:06:58,399
no one is handing
you a glass of water.

119
00:06:59,769 --> 00:07:01,481
Please make sure you give
us a cell phone number...

120
00:07:01,505 --> 00:07:04,689
- Matthew Ruiz? Do you...?
- No one
from the flight has arrived.

121
00:07:04,792 --> 00:07:06,419
- As soon as we get...
- - Do you have a list of people

122
00:07:06,443 --> 00:07:08,587
- they're bringing to the hospital?
- - It can take

123
00:07:08,611 --> 00:07:12,314
Emergency Services quite a long time to move
and identify people in a situation like this.

124
00:07:12,415 --> 00:07:15,633
- Just try to be patient.
- I'm sorry,
my wife was on the plane.

125
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:17,730
- Can you please just...?
- Sir, at this point we don't

126
00:07:17,754 --> 00:07:19,699
have any information.
Please, just sign the sheets.

127
00:07:19,723 --> 00:07:22,919
I'd like to speak to your supervisor,
somebody that knows what's going on.

128
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:26,511
Ma'am, my supervisor doesn't have any
information. Nobody has any information.

129
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:29,731
Please, just sign the sheet.

130
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:34,719
Dr. Hunt! I had way too many
drinks before I told you that.

131
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:36,732
- I didn't mean for...
- Not now, Karev.

132
00:07:36,756 --> 00:07:39,435
Look, I told you that because I didn't
think she should be chief resident,

133
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,804
- not that she should be fired.
- If you didn't
think this through,

134
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:44,061
then you're as dumb as she is.

135
00:07:54,691 --> 00:07:57,258
Hey. You OK?

136
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,694
Yeah, I'm fine. Uh...

137
00:07:59,796 --> 00:08:05,666
The plane was from Baltimore,
where my parents live.

138
00:08:05,769 --> 00:08:08,853
I've taken that flight, uh...

139
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:10,822
with my son.

140
00:08:12,476 --> 00:08:14,316
You want to come sit
down with me for a minute?

141
00:08:16,012 --> 00:08:20,398
No, no, no. I can't, uh,
there's too much, uh...

142
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,683
OK. Um...

143
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:28,156
I'm just gonna stand
here for a minute.

144
00:08:28,258 --> 00:08:29,624
Is that all right?

145
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:38,744
<i>- Are you on any medications?
- - No.</i>

146
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:41,620
- Ever given blood before?
- Nope.

147
00:08:41,722 --> 00:08:45,373
- Any chance you're pregnant?
- Mm...

148
00:08:45,475 --> 00:08:47,275
- I don't know.
- When was your last period?

149
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,911
I'm not sure.

150
00:08:50,013 --> 00:08:54,682
Uh, what were you doing, um, last
time you had to deal with tampons?

151
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,653
Like, maybe it was
St. Patrick's Day,

152
00:08:58,755 --> 00:09:01,689
and you ate, uh, four
green donuts and thought,

153
00:09:01,792 --> 00:09:03,602
"Wow, that's disgusting,
I must be hormonal."

154
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:05,610
Oh, my gosh, you're right!

155
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:09,113
Except it was these gross
cookies with green frosting.

156
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:14,019
But that was a while ago. Uh, I
guess I had mine again around Easter,

157
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:17,855
'cause I was all over the
Marshmallow Peeps. It totally works!

158
00:09:20,928 --> 00:09:24,078
Hey! What the hell?!

159
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:32,036
It looks about six weeks to me.

160
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:35,072
Ahem. I take it this
wasn't deliberate.

161
00:09:37,009 --> 00:09:39,527
- No.
- OK.

162
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:42,613
You want to talk about options?

163
00:09:43,817 --> 00:09:45,583
No.

164
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:50,405
<i>Officials say it's too
early to speculate</i>

165
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:53,725
<i>on the cause of the crash.
But here's what we do know.</i>

166
00:09:53,827 --> 00:09:59,347
<i>The flight originated this morning in
Baltimore carrying 183 passengers</i>

167
00:09:59,449 --> 00:10:02,116
<i>- and 18 crew members...</i>
- Still nobody?

168
00:10:02,218 --> 00:10:05,503
The families are going
crazy. What is taking so long?

169
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,222
Fishing 200 people out of
the water is slow business.

170
00:10:08,324 --> 00:10:09,991
You want to play Angry Birds?

171
00:10:10,093 --> 00:10:12,777
They'll do triage at the
waterfront. Takes time.

172
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:15,774
Actually, with it taking this long,
there's gonna be a lot of hypothermia.

173
00:10:15,798 --> 00:10:18,266
- Kepner!
- Yeah. Warm blankets,
heated lamps

174
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:20,779
- and heated IV fluids. Got it.
- You post chief resident yet?

175
00:10:20,803 --> 00:10:23,855
- No. Not yet.
- What's the hold up?

176
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,674
The suspense ain't killing
me. It's gonna be Grey.

177
00:10:26,776 --> 00:10:29,694
Karev made a great play
for it. A plane full of orphans?

178
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:31,924
- That's pretty impressive.
- He's already decided,

179
00:10:31,948 --> 00:10:35,750
- you don't have to lobby for your boy.
- - Karev.

180
00:10:35,852 --> 00:10:38,714
I want a written account of
exactly what you saw. Every detail.

181
00:10:38,738 --> 00:10:40,149
- When, where...
- Sir, I don't think...

182
00:10:40,173 --> 00:10:43,458
I don't want to
know what you think.

183
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:47,428
I need more sedatives. The people we're
transferring are starting to freak out.

184
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:57,956
You're a good man, Avery.

185
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:04,863
Lexie's yours. Take
her. Take care of her.

186
00:11:06,316 --> 00:11:07,449
I'll stay out of your way.

187
00:11:07,551 --> 00:11:09,991
I kind of already
have her, but...

188
00:11:11,487 --> 00:11:14,322
- thank you?
- You're welcome.

189
00:11:16,743 --> 00:11:18,059
I need to talk to you.

190
00:11:22,766 --> 00:11:25,110
You know, I think I'm gonna order
pizza. If you want I can get the...

191
00:11:25,134 --> 00:11:26,701
I'm pregnant.

192
00:11:33,093 --> 00:11:36,010
- Cristina.
- I cannot believe
this is happening.

193
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,813
I know.

194
00:11:38,915 --> 00:11:42,784
I know it's complicated. I know it
wasn't supposed to happen like this,

195
00:11:42,886 --> 00:11:47,021
but... Cristina, this
could be something...

196
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:48,723
What? No.

197
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,305
There is no way we're
doing this. Do you hear me?

198
00:11:52,329 --> 00:11:56,464
- Cristina...
- No, I am not
this beautiful vessel

199
00:11:56,566 --> 00:11:58,800
for all that might be
good about the future.

200
00:11:58,902 --> 00:12:00,952
I am not carrying your
hopes and dreams, no!

201
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:03,404
I get to talk! I'm here!
There's two of us.

202
00:12:03,506 --> 00:12:08,843
We are a partnership. Can we
just think together? Is that OK?

203
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:17,045
I know who you are. I know
what you want. I love you.

204
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:22,273
I don't love the incubating
potential of your womb, I love you.

205
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:25,827
Why would I want to do something
that would make you miserable?

206
00:12:25,929 --> 00:12:29,680
You think I love you more when you're
miserable? Do you think I want that?

207
00:12:29,783 --> 00:12:33,084
You running off to Meredith? You
think I'm looking for more of that?

208
00:12:35,021 --> 00:12:38,740
- But... I think
there's a way...
- No! No!

209
00:12:38,842 --> 00:12:41,142
I still get to talk. There is
a way to make this work

210
00:12:41,244 --> 00:12:45,212
without it ruining your life
or derailing your career.

211
00:12:45,314 --> 00:12:46,864
I don't want a baby.

212
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:49,100
Well, you have one.

213
00:12:50,703 --> 00:12:52,437
Are...

214
00:12:52,539 --> 00:12:57,842
- Are you getting
all lifey on me?
- How late are you?

215
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:01,446
- That does not matter!
- Of course it matters.

216
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:04,360
OK, fine. You tell me when life begins.
You know, I can't wait to hear this one.

217
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:08,552
I don't know. Does
it have hands?

218
00:13:08,655 --> 00:13:12,273
- I cannot believe
you're doing this!
- I'm just asking a question.

219
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:16,710
I don't want one.

220
00:13:16,812 --> 00:13:19,713
I don't hate children.
I respect children.

221
00:13:19,815 --> 00:13:22,150
I think they should have
parents who want them.

222
00:13:22,252 --> 00:13:23,551
I want them.

223
00:13:24,754 --> 00:13:26,498
I want them, and
maybe you could, too.

224
00:13:26,522 --> 00:13:31,492
