00:28:39,184 --> 00:28:41,851
You want to be with
someone that you love.

453
00:28:45,858 --> 00:28:48,275
So we're booked on
a 9am flight tomorrow.

454
00:28:48,377 --> 00:28:51,094
Let's just spend the
night in some fancy hotel,

455
00:28:51,196 --> 00:28:53,697
just never get out of the bath.

456
00:28:55,333 --> 00:28:56,650
You OK?

457
00:28:59,538 --> 00:29:05,075
Derek, I understand that you don't
want to talk to me, but this is important.

458
00:29:05,177 --> 00:29:06,810
I need to talk to you.

459
00:29:06,912 --> 00:29:10,880
I'm your wife. You
need to call me back.

460
00:29:17,923 --> 00:29:20,490
Does anyone know where there's
a nurse or an information person?

461
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:24,160
- She should be right back.
- My daughter was in the crash.

462
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:26,502
They said she had to have
surgery. Are we supposed to...?

463
00:29:26,532 --> 00:29:29,332
- You're Mrs. Gordon.
- Yes. Sarah Gordon is my...

464
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:33,202
They're still operating. The doctors
have been here every half hour.

465
00:29:33,305 --> 00:29:36,206
- They'll be here any minute.
- Say, would you
like some coffee?

466
00:29:36,308 --> 00:29:38,525
- I'll get it.
- Here, sit down.

467
00:29:38,627 --> 00:29:43,780
- You must have
been driving like crazy.
- I don't under... Are you...?

468
00:29:43,882 --> 00:29:45,365
We heard she was alone.

469
00:29:45,467 --> 00:29:49,069
I thought, as a parent, if
my child was here alone, I...

470
00:29:49,188 --> 00:29:52,956
We all thought that she should
have someone pulling for her.

471
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:58,612
Thank you. That's incredible.

472
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:06,903
Diapers. Swaddle blankets.

473
00:30:07,573 --> 00:30:10,039
And formula.

474
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:12,909
These little bottles are
good for the diaper bag.

475
00:30:13,011 --> 00:30:15,228
- You have a diaper bag?
- No.

476
00:30:15,330 --> 00:30:17,847
We'll get you one, we've
got a few in the NICU closet.

477
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:21,401
We have all this gear. The parents
come in, the baby doesn't make it,

478
00:30:21,503 --> 00:30:24,471
they don't want to see the
stuff, so they just leave it behind.

479
00:30:24,573 --> 00:30:30,560
Now, here's the pacifiers.
She likes the green ones.

480
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:32,624
Is your husband putting
the car seat in the car?

481
00:30:32,648 --> 00:30:35,598
I don't have a car seat. I'm
not even sure I have a husband.

482
00:30:35,701 --> 00:30:40,069
Surgeons, right? You probably forget
what he looks like without a mask.

483
00:30:40,171 --> 00:30:43,691
We'll get you one. You're probably
gonna need a portacrib, too.

484
00:30:43,792 --> 00:30:46,159
I'm gonna throw in
some more diaper cream.

485
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:49,229
She went with her dad
to visit her grandparents.

486
00:30:49,331 --> 00:30:52,099
He had to stay, so he
put her on the plane.

487
00:30:52,201 --> 00:30:55,569
And there was a flight
attendant that watched her,

488
00:30:55,670 --> 00:30:59,005
and was supposed to walk her to
her connecting flight in Vancouver.

489
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:01,124
You never imagine...

490
00:31:02,344 --> 00:31:04,711
I'm sorry.

491
00:31:04,813 --> 00:31:07,997
I never even asked, you
had someone on the plane.

492
00:31:11,853 --> 00:31:13,853
My son, Matthew.

493
00:31:15,307 --> 00:31:16,723
Is he in surgery, too?

494
00:31:21,163 --> 00:31:23,163
Yes.

495
00:31:27,269 --> 00:31:32,673
- Will he be OK?
- Yes. He will.

496
00:31:35,176 --> 00:31:38,211
Sarah's out of surgery.
You can come see her now.

497
00:31:58,617 --> 00:32:00,250
I'm gonna pray for your son.

498
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,580
Hey.

499
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:32,593
Can you stand up?

500
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:34,735
I thought I was
pretty clear, Teddy.

501
00:32:34,837 --> 00:32:37,031
Just shut up and stand
up. I have to do something

502
00:32:37,055 --> 00:32:39,389
and I can't do it while
you're lying in a hospital bed.

503
00:32:39,491 --> 00:32:41,402
I don't want a goodbye hug.
It's gonna make you feel better,

504
00:32:41,426 --> 00:32:43,793
- it's not gonna make me feel...
- Can you just stand up?

505
00:33:10,205 --> 00:33:13,039
You're my husband, and...

506
00:33:15,343 --> 00:33:18,478
and I think I'm falling
in love with you.

507
00:33:36,814 --> 00:33:39,682
Hey. How you doing?

508
00:33:39,784 --> 00:33:41,617
- Not now, Mark.
- Come on, Lexie.

509
00:33:41,719 --> 00:33:45,905
- You've been
in the dead zone all day.
- You have to stop.

510
00:33:46,007 --> 00:33:48,908
You gotta stop talking to
me and checking on me

511
00:33:49,010 --> 00:33:50,777
and talking to my boyfriend.

512
00:33:52,414 --> 00:33:55,782
I love you, and I'm
always gonna love you.

513
00:33:55,884 --> 00:33:59,269
But I don't want to love
you, I want to be happy.

514
00:33:59,371 --> 00:34:01,104
And Jackson makes me happy,

515
00:34:01,206 --> 00:34:06,742
and if you keep pulling at
me, I'm... I'll come back to you.

516
00:34:08,347 --> 00:34:11,114
You're right. I'm sorry.

517
00:34:11,216 --> 00:34:14,418
You got what you wanted.
You wanted a family.

518
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:16,686
Please, just let me
have what I want.

519
00:34:16,789 --> 00:34:18,069
I said you're right.

520
00:34:18,156 --> 00:34:20,740
I told Avery I
was letting you go.

521
00:34:20,843 --> 00:34:23,960
- Did he tell you that part?
- Yeah, it's
paternalistic and weird.

522
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,595
I'm letting you go, Lexie.

523
00:34:26,781 --> 00:34:28,981
That means you gotta...

524
00:34:29,917 --> 00:34:31,618
walk away.

525
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:43,563
Chief friggin'
resident. Unbelievable.

526
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:48,368
- I'm sorry.
- What? Don't be. You deserve it.

527
00:34:48,470 --> 00:34:49,885
I'm happy.

528
00:34:52,257 --> 00:34:54,657
- I have what I want.
- It's been such a crappy year.

529
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:57,376
I can't believe
we're both happy.

530
00:34:57,478 --> 00:34:59,540
I can't believe they like me
enough to make me chief resident.

531
00:34:59,564 --> 00:35:02,893
They hated me for so long. I can't
believe I actually have friends here.

532
00:35:02,917 --> 00:35:04,850
Well, they're gonna
hate you again.

533
00:35:04,952 --> 00:35:08,889
It's now your job to
boss them around.

534
00:35:08,991 --> 00:35:11,123
You know how
much they love that.

535
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:14,177
Oh, God. Is that true?

536
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:17,630
That's true!

537
00:35:20,919 --> 00:35:24,154
OK, so this is the house.

538
00:35:24,256 --> 00:35:26,722
There's another house, where
you're gonna have your own room,

539
00:35:26,825 --> 00:35:30,109
but that, right now, is
just wood and no walls,

540
00:35:30,212 --> 00:35:33,313
so we're gonna stay
here for a while. Derek?

541
00:35:34,683 --> 00:35:38,518
OK. He might be AWOL,
he's had a bad day

542
00:35:38,620 --> 00:35:41,153
and he's a little...

543
00:35:42,657 --> 00:35:46,759
pissed off right now,
but we're gonna be fine.

544
00:35:46,861 --> 00:35:50,129
So we had a big plan
if this ever worked out.

545
00:35:50,232 --> 00:35:54,767
We were gonna have a lullaby from Malawi
to make everything feel homey for you.

546
00:35:54,869 --> 00:35:58,871
To be honest, right now I can't
even think of an American lullaby.

547
00:35:59,791 --> 00:36:01,691
Lexie?

548
00:36:06,231 --> 00:36:09,632
You know, a lot of people live
here. It gets kind of crazy sometimes,

549
00:36:09,734 --> 00:36:12,369
and it's usually not this quiet.

550
00:36:16,074 --> 00:36:17,290
Alex?

551
00:36:27,452 --> 00:36:29,202
OK.

552
00:36:30,338 --> 00:36:33,006
We're gonna be OK.

553
00:36:33,108 --> 00:36:37,710
You and I, we're a team, right?
We're tough. We have that in common.

554
00:36:39,981 --> 00:36:42,115
I am very glad you're here.

555
00:36:42,217 --> 00:36:45,718
I didn't think your first day
was gonna be quite like this.

556
00:36:45,821 --> 00:36:50,990
But I'm gonna get it together,
and we are gonna figure it out.

557
00:37:02,687 --> 00:37:04,654
Tell me how much you love me.

558
00:37:04,756 --> 00:37:08,758
I...

559
00:37:10,495 --> 00:37:13,329
I love you a very great deal.

560
00:37:13,432 --> 00:37:16,182
A lot.

561
00:37:16,284 --> 00:37:20,870
You love me so much. I
want you to remember that.

562
00:37:27,845 --> 00:37:32,081
I made an appointment
to terminate the pregnancy.

563
00:37:33,669 --> 00:37:36,069
- You...
- I'm sorry if this upsets you.

564
00:37:36,171 --> 00:37:39,856
I'm sorry if this isn't
what you wanted, but...

565
00:37:39,958 --> 00:37:43,960
I cannot talk about it anymore.
I... need to lie down. I feel like crap.

566
00:37:44,062 --> 00:37:48,281
This is a marriage.
I tied my life to you.

567
00:37:48,383 --> 00:37:50,150
You don't decide
this without me!

568
00:37:50,252 --> 00:37:53,219
- Do you see me standing here?
- My head is killing me.

569
00:37:53,321 --> 00:37:57,356
You give in a marriage,
you make sacrifices.

570
00:37:57,458 --> 00:38:00,510
I have made many. And I am
asking you to do something for me.

571
00:38:00,612 --> 00:38:04,063
Could you simply consider
doing something for me?

572
00:38:04,165 --> 00:38:08,501
Have a baby? This isn't pizza versus
Thai, you don't give a little on a baby.

573
00:38:08,603 --> 00:38:12,589
- Cristina, I am asking you...
- I'm saying no!

574
00:38:30,758 --> 00:38:31,941
Get out.

575
00:38:33,911 --> 00:38:37,913
Are you...? Because
I'm denying you a baby...

576
00:38:38,016 --> 00:38:40,383
Because you denied
me part of the decision.

577
00:38:40,485 --> 00:38:42,618
Because you denied
me a marriage.

578
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:45,488
- Oh, how dare you!
- Get out!

579
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:52,762
- Hi.
- Hey.

580
00:38:52,864 --> 00:38:58,468
I'm gonna go. I just
wanted to say good night.

581
00:38:59,854 --> 00:39:01,487
I wanna come home with you.

582
00:39:01,589 --> 00:39:05,958
N... No, I can't. Um,
Tuck's with me tonight.

583
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:08,862
I can meet your son. I'm
not gonna bite your son.

584
00:39:08,964 --> 00:39:11,831
No, it's just not
the right time.

585
00:39:11,933 --> 00:39:14,451
- I can't...
- This is a relationship.

586
00:39:14,553 --> 00:39:17,904
Things today were bad. We lean
on each other when things are bad.

587
00:39:18,006 --> 00:39:19,683
That information's not
gonna hurt your child.

588
00:39:19,707 --> 00:39:22,358
And if it does, then this is not
the right relationship for me.

589
00:39:23,845 --> 00:39:27,197
I can control myself in your
house. I'm not gonna touch you.

590
00:39:27,299 --> 00:39:29,465
- OK.
- You can tell
him I'm your friend.

591
00:39:29,550 --> 00:39:32,869
- Tell him whatever you need to.
- OK!

592
00:39:37,758 --> 00:39:38,924
OK.

593
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:05,179
Oh. I was hoping you were Derek.

594
00:40:05,203 --> 00:40:06,552
Sorry.

595
00:40:06,654 --> 00:40:09,222
Well, he took off, and the
hospital gave me a baby.

596
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:12,258
She's upstairs sleeping in
some dead kid's portacrib.

597
00:40:13,427 --> 00:40:15,661
Wow. Uh...

598
00:40:15,763 --> 00:40:19,298
I'm getting an abortion and Owen
just kicked me out of my house.

599
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:22,168
- What? You're...?
- Pregnant.

600
00:40:22,270 --> 00:40:24,437
- And you're...?
- Getting an abortion.

601
00:40:24,539 --> 00:40:28,040
Well... Why didn't you tell me?

602
00:40:29,694 --> 00:40:31,260
You had a busy, busy day.

603
00:40:31,362 --> 00:40:34,580
<i>There's a reason I
said I'd be happy alone.</i>

604
00:40:37,018 --> 00:40:41,253
- Come upstairs. I need help.
- I... I can't.

605
00:40:42,157 --> 00:40:43,522
I've gotta lie down.

606
00:40:43,624 --> 00:40:47,092
<i>It wasn't 'cause I thought
I'd be happy alone.</i>

607
00:40:50,664 --> 00:40:56,319
<i>It was because I thought if I loved
someone, and then it fell apart...</i>

608
00:40:58,123 --> 00:41:00,323
<i>I might not make it.</i>

609
00:41:01,893 --> 00:41:04,427
Tell me not to go to Africa.

610
00:41:06,031 --> 00:41:08,431
Alex.

611
00:41:08,533 --> 00:41:10,166
Go to hell.

612
00:41:13,538 --> 00:41:16,372
<i>It's easier to be alone.</i>

613
00:41:18,043 --> 00:41:21,311
<i>Because what if you
learn that you need love...</i>

614
00:41:22,814 --> 00:41:25,681
<i>and then you don't have it?</i>

615
00:41:25,783 --> 00:41:27,817
<i>What if you like it?</i>

616
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:30,954
<i>And lean on it?</i>

617
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:36,492
<i>What if you shape
your life around it,</i>

618
00:41:36,594 --> 00:41:38,661
<i>and then...</i>

619
00:41:41,432 --> 00:41:44,433
<i>it falls apart?</i>

620
00:41:44,535 --> 00:41:46,870
<i>Can you even survive
that kind of pain?</i>

621
00:41:49,774 --> 00:41:52,591
<i>Losing love is
like organ damage.</i>

622
00:41:54,729 --> 00:41:57,330
<i>It's like dying.</i>

623
00:42:00,769 --> 00:42:03,219
<i>The only difference is...</i>

624
00:42:04,723 --> 00:42:06,856
<i>death ends.</i>

625
00:42:08,226 --> 00:42:09,726
<i>This...</i>

626
00:42:11,896 --> 00:42:13,763
<i>it could go on forever.</i>
